{% include 'layouts/partials/header.njk' %}
<section id="intro">
    <div class="grid col-auto sm:grid-cols-2 mb-2">
        <div class="sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <p>
                <span class="text-lg font-sans font-semibold">Hi, I'm Ed Marsh</span>. This site is my portfolio. I've created concise, consistent, and accessible
                <a href="/skills/technical-writing/">technical content</a>
                for over three decades by incorporating
                <a href="/skills/information-architecture/">information architecture</a>,
                <a href="/skills/content-strategy/">content strategy</a>, and
                <a href="/skills/community/">community building</a>.</p>
            <p>I'm passionate about continuous learning, IndyCar, and the Oxford (serial) comma. I specialize in building or
                revamping documentation practices, which involves:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside">
                <li>Assessing your current content situation.</li>
                <li>Defining
                    <a href="/skills/information-architecture/">structure</a>.</li>
                <li>Implementing
                    <a href="skills/content-strategy/">content strategy</a>.</li>
                <li>
                    <a href="skills/community/">Engaging the people</a>
                    in your organization who are passionate about content.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-6">I
                <a href="/static-site-transformation/">rebuilt this site from the ground up</a>
                to show how I can work with developers and stakeholders to help organizations with all aspects of their content.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg max-w-48">
            <img
                src="/assets/images/ed-marsh.jpg"
                alt="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
                title="Ed Marsh, photo courtesy Arclight Images"
                data-pagefind-meta="image[{{ item.data.cover }}], image_alt[{{ item.data.coverAlt or item.data.title }}]"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
{% set collectionName = "skills" %}
<section class="mx-auto" id="{{ collectionName }}">
    <h2>How I can help you</h2>
    <p class="description text-jet-100">Here are the biggest ways I can impact your organization.
        <a href="/skills/">See all the ways I can help</a>.</p>
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1">
        {% set featured = collections[collectionName] | filterBy("data.featured", true) %}
        {% set sortedFeatured = featured | sort(false, false, "data.featuredOrder") %}
        {% for item in sortedFeatured %}
            {% if loop.index0 < 4 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
{% set collectionName = "blog" %}
<section id="{{ collectionName }}">
    <h2>Blog&thinsp;&mdash;&thinsp;Creating a static site</h2>
    <p class="description text-jet-100">I updated and simplified my old WordPress site using the
        <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/">Eleventy static site generator</a>. Here's how I can use the lessons learned to help you meet your content goals.
        <span class="col-span-full text-lg font-bold italic">
            <a href="/static-site-transformation/">Check back frequently to read the full series!</a>
        </span>
    </p>
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1">
        {% set featured = collections[collectionName] | filterBy("data.featured", true) %}
        {% set sortedFeatured = featured | sort(false, false, "data.featuredOrder") %}
        {% for item in sortedFeatured %}
            {% if loop.index0 < 4 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
{% set collectionName = "podcasts" %}
<section id="{{ collectionName }}">
    <h2>Recent podcasts</h2>
    <p class="description text-jet-100">I'm the jack-of-all-trades for the
        <a href="podcasts/">Content Content podcast</a>, where I interview &ldquo;the people behind the content&rdquo; in
            technical communication, content strategy, content marketing, implementation, and more. Check out
        <span class="text-lg italic">
            <a href="/podcasts/">all of the amazing people I spoke with.</a>
        </span>
    </p>
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1">
        {% set filtered_collections = collections.podcasts %}
        {% for item in filtered_collections | sort(false, false, "data.date") | reverse %}
            {% if loop.index0 <= 3 %}
                {% include 'layouts/partials/card.njk' %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
{% include 'layouts/partials/footer.njk' %}